<h3>ABOUT OBLIGE</h3>

OBLIGE is a random level maker for a bunch of classic FPS games.
Just press a few buttons and <i>kazam!</i> out pops some fun maps
to play.
Well that's our goal anyway, it may take a while to fully achieve it.

<p>
OBLIGE is <b>Free Software</b>, released under the GNU GPL license.
Please note that it comes with absolutely NO WARRANTY of any kind.
You can read the <a href="http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html">GNU General Public License</a>
for all the legal stuff.


<h3>FEATURES / GOALS</h3>

<p>
OBLIGE will have the following general features which set it apart
from existing programs (like the famous <b>SLIGE</b>
by David Chess)

<ul class="features">
  <li>higher quality levels, e.g. outdoor areas!
  <li>easy to use GUI interface (no messing with command lines)
  <li>built-in node builder, the created levels are ready to play
  <li>uses the LUA scripting language for easy customisation
</ul>

<p>
We plan to fully support the following games:

<ul class="gamelist">
  <li>DOOM and DOOM II
  <li>Heretic
  <li>Hexen
  <li>Quake
</ul>

Other games, such as Quake 2 and Duke Nukem 3D,
might get supported in the future, but for now the
focus is mainly on the games listed above.

<p>
<i>(See the <a href="http://oblige.svn.sourceforge.net/viewvc/oblige/trunk/WISHLIST.txt">WISHLIST</a>
for even more stuff we'd like to add)
</i>


<h3>SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS</h3>

<ul class="sysreq">
<li>Pentium 500 Mhz CPU or higher.
<li>128 MB of RAM or higher.
<li>Windows 2000, XP, Vista or later.  (Linux is supported too)
</ul>


<h3>KNOWN PROBLEMS</h3>

<ul class="status">

<li>no traps, no cages
<li>no secrets, no powerups
<li>very limited scenery
<li>messed up monster quantities

</ul>

